<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 184.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Fish</persName> to <persName type="to">Baron
                                Gerolt</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi><hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-10-19"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 19, 1870.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>The undersigned, Secretary of State of the United States, has the honor
                            to acknowledge the receipt of the communication of the 12th instant,
                            addressed to him by the envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary
                                <pb facs="0265" n="231" xml:id="pg_231"/> of the North German Union,
                            relating to violations of international law alleged to have been
                            perpetrated by French troops.</p>
                        <p>The undersigned avails himself of the occasion to renew to Baron Gerolt
                            the assurance of his highest consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>